body:
You can normalize your [$search](pipe.$search) query score in the range from
`0` to `1` in the subsequent stages of your aggregation pipeline.
You can use the following stages after your [$search](pipe.$search) stage in
the following order to normalize the score:

- [$addFields](manual/reference/operator/aggregation/addFields)

  ```json
  {
     "$addFields": {
     "score": {
         "$meta": "searchScore"
     }
     }
  }
  ```

- [$setWindowFields](manual/reference/operator/aggregation/setWindowFields)

  ```json
  {
     "$setWindowFields": {
     "output": {
         "maxScore": {
         "$max": "$score"
         }
     }
     }
  }
  ```

- [$addFields](manual/reference/operator/aggregation/addFields)

  ```json
  {
     "$addFields": {
     "normalizedScore": {
         "$divide": [
         "$score", "$maxScore"
         ]
     }
     }
  }
  ```

Basic

Arithmetic

Gaussian

Path

Unary

The MongoDB Search results contain the following scores:

- The modified score for the [$search](pipe.$search) query in the `score`
  field from the [$addFields](manual/reference/operator/aggregation/addFields) stage.

- The maximum score assigned to the documents in the results in the
  `maxScore` field from the [$setWindowFields](manual/reference/operator/aggregation/setWindowFields) stage.

- The normalized score in the `normalizedScore` field from the
  [$addFields](manual/reference/operator/aggregation/addFields) stage, which is computed by dividing the
  modified score in `$score` by the maximum score in `$maxScore`
  using [$divide](manual/reference/operator/aggregation/divide).
